:: Costs and other resources involved {"position":"1000,1300","size":"100,100"}
<h1>Costs and Other Resources Involved </h1>
Open access requires time, expertise, and investment. With some planning, that process can cost as little or as much as your organisation can afford.

Using existing platforms like Art UK provides infrastructure for publishing, discovery, and engagement. 

When discussing this as an organisation, consider that maintaining restricted access models is also resource-intensive. 

Art UK’s recommends:
<ul><li>Starting with already digitised public domain works</li>
<li>Using Art UK support for rights assessment and data preparation</li>
<li>Using Art UK as a delivery platform and complement with your own systems, where needed</li>
<li>Updating to more generous resolutions as/when ready</li></ul>  To learn more about the costs associated with going open on Art UK, please get in touch by emailing us at [email@email.com].
<h2>I want to learn more about:</h2>
