:: Digitisation and copyright law in the UK {"position":"575,1300","size":"100,100"}
<h1>Digitisation and copyright law in the UK</h1>
Whether copyright applies to a digitisation primarily depends on the copyright status of the underlying work. 

Guidance from the UK Intellectual Property Office has clarified that simply creating a copy of an older image will not result in a new copyright in the digitised version: 
<blockquote>[A]ccording to established case law, the courts have said that copyright can only subsist in subject matter that is original in the sense that it is the author’s own ‘intellectual creation’. Given this criterion, it seems unlikely that what is merely a retouched, digitised image of an older work can be considered as ‘original’. This is because there will generally be minimal scope for a creator to exercise free and creative choices if their aim is simply to make a faithful reproduction of an existing work.</blockquote>
This means:
<ul><li>If the underlying work is in <strong>copyright</strong>, the digitised work is protected by the same copyright. The digitisation is a copy of the underlying work with its use governed by the copyright’s owner. </li>
<li>If the underlying work is in the <strong>public domain</strong>, the digitised work is also in the public domain. The digitisation does not receive a new copyright because it is not, itself, a new original work.</li></ul> An organisation <strong>does</strong> receive a new copyright for new creative materials produced, such as explanatory text on a title card, exhibition photographs or a research publication. If your organisation owns the rights associated with the materials, you are able to release these digitised assets under an open license if you so choose, such as the licenses produced by Creative Commons.
<h2>I want to learn more about:</h2>
<span class="btn-link-outline"> <a href = "https://www.glamelab.org/products/3d-models-and-rights-management/">The nitty-gritty about copyright law and digitisation, including for 3D models.</a></span>

<span class="btn-link-outline"> <a href = "https://www.heritagefund.org.uk/sites/default/files/media/attachments/Digitisation%20project%20planner%20and%20handbook.pdf">How to plan digitisation projects, with the goal of releasing materials on Art UK and other platforms.</a></span>

