:: Welcome {"position":"700,100","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/6/63/Art_UK_logo.png" alt="Art UK logo"  width="600">

<h1>Welcome to the Art UK Open Access Toolkit </h1> PLACEHOLDER TEXT - Welcome to the Toolkit, etc. 

Are you ready to go open? Let’s find out! 
<h2>What is the toolkit?</h2> This interactive toolkit will introduce you to open access and give you a clearer picture of what it means in practice for you, your organisation and your collections. 

This toolkit is designed to help you:<ul>
<li>Assess your organisation’s readiness to make your images of artworks more openly available</li>
<li>Explore how open access can support your organisation’s public, educational, and strategic aims</li>
<li>Understand key aspects of copyright, the public domain, licensing and risk </li>
<li>Make informed decisions about how and where to adopt open access approaches </li>
<li>Make use of guidance and support available through Art UK and partner initiatives, including support with rights assessment and identifying suitable works</li></ul> This toolkit can be used by anyone at your organisation, from senior decision-makers to those working in curatorial, collections management and engagement roles. 
<h2>What are my options?</h2> At the end of this toolkit, you have three options:
<ol><li><strong>Go open on Art UK:</strong> Release your Art UK images for free reuse at the image size of your choice.</li>
<li><strong>Join the growing open GLAM movement:</strong> In addition, you can bring the open access learnings from the toolkit to your organisation and other collections.</li>
<li><strong>Sit tight, at least for now:</strong> Art UK will direct users to your organisation’s website for the terms on image rights and reuse.</li>
</ol> Before getting started, feel free to take a look at [[all the other organisations]] who have gone open with Art UK. 

You can also jump straight to the [[Open access on display]] section, which goes into more detail about organisations who have taken up open GLAM on Art UK and elsewhere.
<h2>Who should I contact if I have questions?</h2> If you have questions about copyright, image reuse, or open access, you can contact Art UK’s dedicated team at copyright@artuk.org. 

Art UK is happy to review existing permissions and agreements, discuss updates, and help you understand how your images are displayed and made available on the platform. Further guidance on digital skills and image reuse is available on our collection guidance pages.

You can also explore additional resources developed by GLAM-E Lab, including their wider digital skills support and open GLAM toolkit, which provide further insight into open access practice. 
<h2>About</h2> This toolkit has been developed in collaboration by Art UK and the GLAM-E Lab. A special thanks to the National Lottery Heritage Fund, who funded this work. 
This toolkit is not intended to be legal advice. You should always contact a qualified professional for legal support.

