:: open access with Art UK {"position":"550,525","size":"100,100"}
<h1>Open access with Art UK</h1>
Through Art UK, open access will enable you to reach wider audiences, support learning and research, and encourage creative reuse—while improving clarity for users about what they can and cannot do with images. 
<h3>What are we committing to?</h3> At base, this means:
<ul> <li>Placeholder text - [Clarify this is limited to public domain works]</li>
<li> Placeholder text - [Tell orgs what the baseline ask is: for example, X pixels on the longest side as CC0]</li></ul> <h3>What does the programme entail?</h3>
Joining the programme means:: 
<ul><li>[Sell the benefits of the programme]</li>
<li>[Explain the benefits of uploads to Wikimedia Commons, support from Wikipedian in Residence, etc]</li>
<li>[Featured on the Open Access webpage]</li>
<li>[Linking up with other collections through the Art UK cool tools]</li>
<li>[Tracking, any statistics, cool tools, that sort of thing]</li>
<li>[Engagement and educational programming]</li></ul> <h3>What support does Art UK provide?</h3> For collections already on Art UK:
<ul><li>[Explain in concrete terms]</li></ul> For collectings looking to join Art UK, our staff provides practical support to clear rights, explore and implement open access, including:
<ul><li>Rights assessment to identify public domain artworks and assess copyright status</li>
<li>Image sourcing, storage and digital preservation, by hosting copies of the images for your organisation</li>
<li>A trusted platform that hosts and displays images with clear rights information, metadata and attribution</li>
<li>Keywording for more discoverability, engagement tools</li>
<li>Greater visibility through open access marketing and platform features to surface open access images available for the public</li>
<li>Data collection and reporting, from user engagement data to spreadsheets to support internal review and decision making</li>
<li>Guidance and training through access to toolkits and other resources, webinars, and one-to-one support</li>
<li>Agreement and permission support by reviewing and updating any existing agreements and permissions that you have with Art UK</li>
<li>Commercial opportunities through the Art UK Shop for selling collection merchandise, Print-on-demand services, and linking back to your organisations own commercial features</li></ul> The support remains available throughout your partnership with Art UK, at whatever stage of the process for your organisation. 
<h3>Programme specifications</h3>
The following pdfs provide fuller details to support discussions within your organisation:
<ul><li>Programme overview. Placeholder - description.</li>
<li>Technical specifications. Placeholder - description.</li>
<li>Wikimedia UK. Placeholder - description.</li></ul>

[[Welcome]] / [[I need more information about Art UK’s open access project]] / Open access with Art UK




